    "name": "M-Walk",
    "description": "M-Walk is a graph-walking agent designed to solve knowledge base completion by learning paths over a graph toward a target node. It combines a deep recurrent neural network (RNN) with Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS).\n\nThe RNN component encodes the state (the history of the walked path) and maps this encoding separately to both a policy and Q-values. To effectively train the agent despite sparse rewards, M-Walk generates trajectories using MCTS combined with the neural policy, which yields more positive rewards. The network is then improved off-policy via Q-learning on these generated trajectories, modifying the RNN policy through parameter sharing. This proposed RL algorithm iteratively applies this policy-improvement step for learning.\n\nAt test time, MCTS and the neural policy are combined to predict the target node. Experimental results demonstrate that M-Walk learns better policies than other RL methods based primarily on policy gradients, and it also surpasses traditional KBC baselines.",
